# Nimbus/AgentOS — STAGED, INACTIVE. Deterministic gate: hold plasmashell's
# startup until swaync actually owns org.freedesktop.Notifications.
#
# ── Why this exists ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# KDE has NO supported way to disable Plasma's built-in notification server
# (confirmed 2026-06-18 — Nate Graham/ngraham, KDE Discuss "Override built-in
# notification daemon": notifications are a built-in component of plasmashell,
# not a separable service; the only method is "run your notification service
# BEFORE plasmashell starts"). The sibling drop-in `after-swaync.conf` plus
# swaync's `Type=dbus` already implement that — BUT systemd ordering has a leak:
# `After=swaync.service` is satisfied when swaync's start job *finishes*, success
# OR failure. If swaync hard-fails before acquiring the name, plasmashell is
# released and grabs org.freedesktop.Notifications, and swaync can't reclaim it
# (it requests the name without replacement). This gate closes that leak.
#
# ── What it does ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Adds an ExecStartPre that blocks plasmashell's start until swaync is the
# *actual owner* of the name (not merely "someone owns it"). This enforces
# ngraham's rule deterministically: plasmashell only initialises its own
# notification engine after swaync holds the name, so it defers every time.
#
# ── Fail-open / fail-slow tradeoff ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Bounded 30s wait, then `exit 0` REGARDLESS — so a genuinely dead swaync can
# never blank the desktop; plasmashell starts and reclaims notifications (the
# fail-open fallback).
#
# ── This is STAGED, not active ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# systemd only reads `*.conf` drop-ins, so this `.conf.disabled` file is IGNORED.
# Only enable it if the reboot test shows swaync STILL losing the race AFTER the
# portal fix in swaync.service.d/nimbus-race.conf (the v2 root-cause fix). Note
# this gate's 30s wait does NOT cover a 25s+ portal hang on its own — it is a
# complement to the portal fix, not a substitute. Don't stack unvalidated fixes.
#
#   ACTIVATE:  mv gate-on-swaync.conf.disabled gate-on-swaync.conf   (in
#                 ~/.config/systemd/user/plasma-plasmashell.service.d/)
#              systemctl --user daemon-reload      # takes effect next login
#
#   REVERT:    mv gate-on-swaync.conf gate-on-swaync.conf.disabled   (or rm it)
#              systemctl --user daemon-reload
#
# Complementary to `after-swaync.conf` (keep both): that one pulls swaync into
# plasmashell's transaction (Wants=) and orders it (After=); this one makes the
# handoff deterministic.

[Service]
ExecStartPre=/usr/bin/bash -c 'for i in $(seq 1 60); do /usr/bin/busctl --user status org.freedesktop.Notifications 2>/dev/null | /usr/bin/grep -q "Comm=swaync" && exit 0; sleep 0.5; done; exit 0'
